headline: Exclusive-JetBlue negotiates partnership with United Airlines, sources say
summary: CHICAGO (Reuters) -JetBlue Airways and United Airlines have been negotiating a partnership, three industry sources familiar with the matter told Reuters.  The New York-based airline has been seeking partnerships after a federal judge blocked its so-called Northeast Alliance with American Airlines in 2023.  The partnership with United is envisioned as quite different from the NEA, the sources said.

headline: JetBlue pulls earnings outlook amid tariff uncertainty, following American and Delta
summary: JetBlue pulls its guidance, and US travel demand takes a hit from trade war uncertainty.
